            "last_activity_date": 1571049250,
            "creation_date": 1571049250,
            "body": "<p>You can define a new <code>ApplicationRunner<\/code> bean in tests with <code>@Order(Ordered.HIGHEST_PRECEDENCE)<\/code><\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 58374932,
            "question_id": 58374795
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/f14f4aeffe45c2b661a7c5a16f7ed1f0?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
                "account_id": 5247691,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 4192839,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/4192839/cybermafia",
                "reputation": 327,
                "display_name": "CyberMafia"
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 4.0",
            "score": 1,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1571049390,
            "creation_date": 1571049390,
            "body": "<p>Multiple <strong>ApplicationRunner<\/strong> beans can be defined within the same application context and can be ordered using the Ordered interface or @Order annotation. Use one for your testing.<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 58374973,
            "question_id": 58374795
        }
